<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddd259fed-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s4722"><num value="4722">§ 4722.</num><heading> Mandatory Senate ethics training for Members and staff</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="iddd259fee-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s4722/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Training program</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Select Committee on Ethics shall conduct ongoing ethics training and awareness programs for Members of the Senate and Senate staff.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="iddd259fef-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s4722/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Requirements</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The ethics training program conducted by the Select Committee on Ethics shall be completed by—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="iddd259ff0-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s4722/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> new Senators or staff not later than 60 days after commencing service or employment; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="iddd259ff1-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s4722/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> Senators and Senate staff serving or employed on <date date="2007-09-14">September 14, 2007</date>, not later than 165 days after <date date="2007-09-14">September 14, 2007</date>.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="iddd259ff2-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">(<ref href="/us/pl/110/81/tV/s553">Pub. L. 110–81, title V, § 553</ref>, <date date="2007-09-14">Sept. 14, 2007</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/121/773">121 Stat. 773</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
